5:
Listen up, team! I wanna thank you
all for your hard work prepping for
the school's grand reopening and
the graduation ceremony! And
since tomorrow's the big day, that
means...
9:
Tonight, we PAR-TAY! So let loose,
but not TOO loose, 'kay? We don't
want anyone being too hungover to
attend, so take it easy!
15:
Hey, dum-dums! She said take it
EASY! Don't forget about the
graduation ceremony tomorrow!
19:
All right, I suppose I'll have a sip...
Cheers!
22:
Could you, uh, stop staring at me
like that? You're making it hard to
drink...
27:
Haha, cut us some slack. We've all
been waiting to have a drink with
you for a long time.
31:
Well? How does it taste? They say
you never forget your first time.
35:
Hmm... The smell isn't too bad... Huh.
I can kinda feel it, I guess?
40:
Sounds like we have a drinker! Elise
is going to be so happy to hear this.
44:
Don't go drinkin' yourself under the
table, now.
49:
Be careful, Alk... And tell us right
away if you begin to feel ill!
54:
Guys, please. Just because I died
once doesn't mean you have to
treat me like a baby...
58:
My, my... It seems the festivities have
already begun. Perhaps I should
have arrived a bit earlier.
61:
You all seem rosy-faced and
merry... Pardon my intrusion.
69:
Fragments of Western Yamato have
begun merging again. Yamato will
require my attention for the
foreseeable future.
72:
I won't be able to spare the time to
visit you all for quite some time, so I
wanted to be sure to say my
goodbyes. Especially considering
the great debt I owe you and this
city.
80:
So, Alk... What are your plans from
here on out?
84:
I can teach you a fighting move or
two, if you'd like. One one-eyed
warrior to another.
89:
Piss off, pal. He's had enough
fighting for one life
93:
Nimbus. I know it must've been hard,
seeing what you saw... But you can't
keep protecting Alk forever. You
know that.
98:
Hey, now! What's with all the long
faces, huh?! This is a CELEBRATION,
for cryin' out loud!
103:
Haha! Apologies, Alk. As you can
see, we're already a teeeensy bit
drunk at the moment.
107:
It's fine, Taichi. As long as you take
that overly chummy bucket of bolts
back with you!
116:
I would say I'm precisely as chummy
as our relationship demands! Haha.
121:
Give him a break. His precious little
songbird was taken away from him.
Least you can do is let him get drunk!
137:
Geezers like us tend to get lost in the
past when the drinks start flowin'...
141:
But Alk, my boy... What're you doin'
here? Shouldn't you be over there?
146:
Can you believe it? I actually grew
taller!
150:
And Stella, too! This has never
happened before!
154:
Yeah, yeah. We know. You've only
told us, like, a thousand times. That's
great, good for you. Geez...
159:
Have your interviews been going
well, Stella?
164: Yes. I only have a few more to go.
167:
But I've been wanting to ask all of
you, toowhat are your plans for
the future?
171:
Me? Nothing much, I guess. People
are still coming through the
Kaleidoscope, so I'll probably help
them out.
176:
I'll be assisting with the restoration
of the city. I promised myself that I
would do everything in my power to
help the people here.
180:
I've been thinking about helping out
Dia and the androids... but I'm still on
the fence.
183:
Part of me thinks that maybe I'd be
better off traveling on my own for a
while.
187:
Like, some kinda journey to "find
yourself" or whatever?
191:
Uh, well... Hm... I guess you could say
that.
194:
I just... want to know who I am.
There's so much of myself hidden
below the surface that even I don't
understand yet.
197:
I want to try new things. Get to
understand myself. Even if I get hurt
in the process... I'm used to it.
207:
I don't enjoy it, no. What I'm trying to
say is... I think it's important to love
yourself.
213:
Don't worry. I know we're all going to
be okay.
216:
I learned so much from you all. Even
if we're apart, we won't be alone.
219:
Our memories we made together
will never disappear. We'll step into
the future and make new memories
to treasure, too.
223:
And that's something I can be glad
about. From the bottom of my heart!
226:
So now I want to ask you, Nephtim.
What does the future hold for you?
235: And that dream is to go to school.
238:
Preparations now complete:
Nephtim's schoolgirl glow-up
confirmed to be straight fire.
Nephtim will take Shibuya by storm.
243:
What the hell?! Weren't you totally
anti-graduation like, yesterday?!
247:
Termination directive: abandoned.
Nephtim is pumped for school life
with friends.
251:
Nephtim and the gang are going to
flex on all the haters. Yay!
257:
Oh... Oh wow... That uniform... You're
so cute?! Yay?!
261: Heh... Guess I'm a little late for that.
265:
Whatever your future holds, Alk, just
promise you won't end up like the
rest of these jokers.
273:
And just like that, we laughed the
night away until dawn.
277:
The school's grand reopening was
upon us. Graduation day was here
at last.
